cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.CR

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper focuses on vehicle tracking using computer vision and machine learning techniques, which falls under the scope of this sub-category.
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper mentions the use of machine learning in vehicle tracking, which is a key aspect of this sub-category.
3. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper discusses the use of edge nodes across a road network for vehicle tracking, which involves distributed computing and falls under the scope of this sub-category.
4. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper mentions the constraints of bandwidth and latency in vehicle tracking, which are key aspects of networking and internet architecture.
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper briefly mentions privacy concerns in vehicle tracking, which falls under the scope of this sub-category.
